    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">STRATEGY<br />
<br />
First of all, i&#39;d like to point out that it&#39;s my first deck in lotr. Some great cards are still missing, like Hearken to Me or Eowyn&#39;s Sword.<br />
You&#39;ve to know that i&#39;m not playing with Shadow stuff &#39;cause me and my friends decided to begin with the old rules.<br />
I thank you for all consideration to my deck.<br />
<br />
FP : the game is most based on Eomer and Gandalf.<br />
Eowyn can transfer wound to herself and aragorn can heal eomer by signet capability, so eomer can resist a lot. On the other way, there is some ideas in the deck :<br />
- using gamling to put items in skirmish phase, then transfer them (mainly to eomer) in the next company phase.<br />
- merry can either be strong, with his sword, his shield, and sometimes using his powerful capability<br />
- theoden and hretel (obviously mounted) are quite strong too.<br />
<br />
Shadow : fell beast is here to make the deck turn easier, as bent on discovery.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
bid 0, let opponent begin and be hurt by nazgul, then advance carefully in the middle game to finish faster.<br />
